<L>__{exterior pool day}
<A>__{eleanor approaches the pool. it is as quiet as a church. she is stunned to observe over a dozen tables set up in the water. on each table is a child or an adult polio wearing their bathing suit. next to them is a physical therapist also in bathing attire conducting therapy. in hushed tones the physical therapists encourage and work the distressed limbs of the patients as helena swims to each table overseeing the work being done. eleanor sits down in a chair and watches fascinated.}
